title: For Sale:  Berryhill Custom Colt Rail Gun w/extras
postcontent:
Up for sale is probably the nicest 1911 I've ever owned. Two-tone Colt Rail Gun worked over by Dave Berryhill. Dave replaced just about everything this pistol came with originally as far as the internals go. Interested parties can get the full list, but the parts were replaced with various EGW and Wilson BP aftermarket stuff, all hand fitted. It wears VZ Aliens and sports Heinie straight 8 night sights. Even when compared to my bullseye gun, I'm pretty certain this is the best 1911 trigger I have ever felt. Gun probably has about 300-400 rounds through it. Only selling because I'm funding another project and this doesn't get nearly the use it deserves. Comes with Wilson 47D mags-we can talk about how many. Also included is a second extractor (Wilson BP, just like the one in the gun) that Dave tuned in case the first one ever went down.

Also available are a Raven holster for this w/an x300, a few OTG concepts kydex mag pouches, and a bunch of 47D mags. Price listed does not reflect these items.

Could definitely use the cash more than a trade right now, but a newish gen4 G17 could get me interested as far as a partial trade.

title: For Sale:  Will make your custom kydex holster
location: West Virginia, West Virginia, United States
postcontent:
Do you need a custom holster? Shoot me a note and we can discuss. Visit us online: https://www.etsy.com/shop/CazGear?ref=hdr_shop_menu

Inside the Waistband (concealed) and Outside the Waistband carry options available.

Common Questions

How much are your holsters? Our holsters normally run $30 for an average size gun with flat basic colors. Our IWB holsters run $5 more due to a stronger material used.

How much are your mag holsters? Depending on the type, they begin at $24.95. More complicated holsters with various mag types are available.

Can you make a holster for an FNX .45? Yes, that is our specialty, making holsters for large, bulky or rare guns is always a challenge. We aren't happy until you are happy.

What about a Calico M950? Yes, that was one of our most challenging and difficult guns to date.

Do you make holster with custom light/laser attachments? We do not carry "ALL" the custom light/laser attachments and can work with you depending on the model. In most cases, it is easier if you show up with the gear for us to measure and assess the work needed.

What kind of materials do you have? We use Kydex, Holstex, and Bolatron in varying sizes from .60 (thin IWB), .80 (medium IWB and OWB), .93 (Thick OWB) to .125. (OWB and complex projects)

What types of holsters do you make? Inside the waistband (IWB) concealed carry is our specialty but we can make outside the waistband (OWB) as well. We have designed custom mag carriers for 3 Gun competitions to include mag holsters for a Kriss Vector.

What is your most popular holster? Our most notable is our patent pending "switchblade" made especially for concealed carry. Very easy to conceal, you can't even feel its there and is designed for faster extraction than traditional style mag holsters.

One of the screws came loose and I lost it, can you replace it? Yes, we offer lifetime warranties on the holsters and will mail you a replacement to keep you going. We only ask that in certain cases, you pay for shipping costs if required.

Do you make leather holsters? At this time we are not able to make leather holsters but may explore that option at a later date.

Customer Comments:

They didn't have the mold of my firearm but was able to get quickly, complete my order and have it on my doorstep in about a week. Communication with this guy was great, he asked questions and made suggestions to make sure I got exactly what I wanted, the Arondight switchblades are a pretty cool design."

Custom IWB for Ruger LCR 38 (March 5th 2015): "My holster arrived very quickly even though it was the first one they'd made for my particular revolver. It's very well made, and the follow up by them to make sure it's perfect has been fantastic. It's the thinnest inside-the-waistband holster that I have, I'm sure it'll provide great service for years to come :)"

title: For Sale:  Spyderco Military G-10 Black
location: Canton Massillon Navarre Strasburg, Ohio, United States
postcontent: Since the steel is the spirit of the knife, CPM-S30V with almost 2% carbon seemed the logical choice for the blade given its reputation for long-term edge retention and rust resistance. The Military Model, or 'Millie' as it's affectionately known has a modified clip-point blade laser cut with a 14 mm Spyderco Round Hole for quick deployment and for use with gloves. Texturing above the hole hold the thumb in contact with the blade's spine during cutting for confident control over the sharpened edge. The handle scales are G-10 with the lock's liner nested (inlayed) directly into the scale, pumping up lock strength without the addition of bulky liners. Spacers between the scales create a gap running the handle's full length exposing the inside workings for inspection and cleaning. The handle flares slightly at the front end creating a finger choil and at the butt end, which keeps the knife from slipping forward or backward in the hand while making tough or aggressive cuts.
